    • Method Detail

      • putIfAbsent

        public static <K,V> V putIfAbsent(Map<K,V> map,
                                  K key,
                                  V value)
        Backwards compatible Map.putIfAbsent(K, V) to support < Android API 24. If the specified key is not already associated with a value (or is mapped to null) associates it with the given value and returns null, else returns the current value.
        Parameters:
        key - key with which the specified value is to be associated
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with the specified key, or null if there was no mapping for the key.

        Returns:
        object
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if object is null
